&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 x Locum Consultant Psychiatrists, General Adult Psychiatry, St Giles CMHT (Community Mental Health Team), London Borough of Southwark. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Two 10 PA posts available &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The South London and Maudsley NHS Foundation Trust (SLAM) is recruiting to two 10 PA Locum Consultant Psychiatrist posts based in the London Borough of Southwark (St Giles CMHT) and within walking distance of The Maudsley Hospital. These positions have arisen as a result of the career progression of the substantive consultants. The successful applicants will provide medical leadership to well established community mental health teams and have the opportunity to lead the teams through Southwark’s community transformation project focusing on delivering care in line with the NHS Long Term Plan. The posts will be advertised substantively when reconfiguration is complete.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SLAM is one of three Foundation Trusts within Kings Health Partners Academic Health Sciences Centre and is committed to innovation, effective interventions and improved service user outcomes. As well as providing excellent mental health services for the local community. The Trust is committed to maintaining its national status as a provider of specialist mental health services for people living across the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Marta Dell’Aringa - Associate Medical Director&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Marta.DellAringa@slam.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
